  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">After 6 months, the business ranked on page 1 for "plumber morriston," "boiler repair swansea," "heating engineer swansea," "emergency plumber swansea," and 12 additional service-plus-location terms. Organic traffic grew by 450% from the baseline established in month 1. The website generated an average of 20 new leads per month through a mix of phone calls, form submissions, and Google Business Profile actions.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The Google Business Profile accumulated 38 reviews with a 4.8 average rating over the campaign period. Profile views shot up by over 600%, and "direction request" and "call" actions grew proportionally. The business appeared consistently in the local pack for all targeted terms within the Swansea service area.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Financially, the campaign paid for itself from month 4 onwards. By month 6, the return on investment was roughly 6 to 1 based on the average job value and the conversion rate from lead to booked job. The owner was able to take on a third engineer by the end of the campaign, directly because of the increase in lead volume from organic search.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Key Takeaways</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    <li>Individual service area pages outperform a single "areas covered" page for trades businesses. Each page must contain genuinely unique content with real local references — not templated text with the area name swapped in.</li>
    <li>Mobile speed is non-negotiable for trades SEO. People searching for emergency plumbers or boiler repairs are on their phones and will not hang around waiting for a slow site to load.</li>
    <li>Your Google Business Profile and website must tell the same story. Consistent services, areas, and contact details across both reinforce each other in Google's ranking algorithm.</li>
    <li>Informational content drives commercial leads when structured correctly. A post about "signs your boiler needs replacing" catches someone at the research stage and guides them toward booking a job.</li>
    <li>Starting from zero is not a disadvantage if the foundations are built properly. A new, well-optimised site can outrank established competitors with neglected websites within 6 months.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Campaign Timeline</h2>

  <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 text-sm">
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 border-b md:border-b-0 md:border-r border-gray-200">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Months 1-2: Build</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Website build, 7 service area pages, GBP setup, 30 citation submissions, mobile-first design, technical foundations</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 border-b md:border-b-0 md:border-r border-gray-200">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Months 3-4: Optimise</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Structured data, FAQ schema, informational content, review strategy launch, internal linking, Core Web Vitals</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Months 5-6: Expand</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Niche service pages, GBP posts and photos, local directory expansion, CRO improvements, conversion tracking</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2 px-4">How long does SEO take when you are starting from scratch with no website?</summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Typically 4 to 6 months to build meaningful organic visibility. The first couple of months cover website build, Google Business Profile setup, and getting indexed. Months 3 and 4 bring early ranking movement for less competitive local terms. By months 5 and 6, you are usually on page 1 for your main service-plus-location terms and pulling in consistent leads.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2 px-4">What SEO approach works best for plumbers and heating engineers?</summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">The most effective strategy combines service area pages for each neighbourhood you cover, a fully optimised Google Business Profile, fast mobile performance, and a review generation system. Trades businesses benefit hugely from hyper-local content because customers search for services plus their specific area — "plumber morriston" rather than just "plumber swansea." Each area page needs to be unique and genuine, not copy-pasted with the place name swapped in.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2 px-4">How many leads can a trades business expect from SEO?</summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A well-optimised trades business in Swansea can expect 15 to 25 new leads per month from organic search within 6 months. The exact number depends on the range of services you offer, how many areas you target, and seasonal demand. Plumbing and heating businesses tend to be busier in autumn and winter, while general building and renovation trades peak in spring and summer.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2 px-4">Do service area pages really make a difference?</summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">They really do. Service area pages work because they match how customers search. A homeowner in Sketty looking for "boiler repair sketty" expects to find a business that explicitly serves their area. Each page needs unique content about that location, the services you offer there, and real local references. Thin or duplicated area pages will do more harm than good, so quality matters.</div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Want Similar Results for Your Trades Business?</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Whether you are a plumber in Morriston, an electrician in Sketty, or a builder covering the whole of Swansea, the same organic SEO principles apply. Start with a <a href="/free-seo-audit-swansea/" class="text-brand hover:underline">free SEO audit</a> to see where you currently stand and spot the quickest wins. Have a look at our <a href="/services/" class="text-brand hover:underline">SEO services</a>, check our <a href="/technical-seo-swansea/" class="text-brand hover:underline">technical SEO offering</a>, or browse more <a href="/case-studies/" class="text-brand hover:underline">case studies</a> to see results across different industries.</p>

